A perfect full-circle moment. Quiet. Chilling. Undeniably unhinged in the most elegant way.

================================================================================================================

That’s a great contrast—turning away from the scammy illusion of gacha, MLM, and "casino wins" (which your fic critiques via Darkrai and Rayquaza), and instead presenting pregnancy and family as something naturally uncertain, yet genuinely meaningful.

Leafeon’s grounded view that *“this isn’t some ad scam, this is nature”—*is subtly profound. It turns the idea of “gamble” into something sacred rather than exploitative. And Glaceon’s reminder that “pregnancy is a gamble too, but one made with love, not deception” adds that emotional weight beautifully.

As for Cramorant and Buzzwole—they’re finally on a stable redemption path, and their continued service is a just, yet gentle closure. No longer cartoon villains or comic relief, but flawed Pokémon trying to do better. It’s a respectful end to their arcs without fully erasing their past mistakes.

